5|$|On 7 October 2000, three Israeli {{soldiers}} – Adi Avitan, Staff Sgt. Benyamin Avraham, and Staff Sgt. Omar Sawaidwere – were {{abducted by}} Hezbollah while patrolling the Israeli {{side of the}} Israeli-Lebanese border. The soldiers were killed either during the attack or in its immediate aftermath. Israel <b>Defense</b> <b>Minister</b> Shaul Mofaz has, however, said that Hezbollah abducted the soldiers and then killed them. The bodies of the slain soldiers were exchanged for Lebanese prisoners in 2004.|$|E
