50|$|Due to {{the great}} {{importance}} of the <b>defense</b> portfolio, prime <b>ministers</b> have often held the position {{in addition to their}} prime ministerial duties; seven of the sixteen <b>Defense</b> <b>Ministers</b> to date were also serving Prime Ministers. Five of them (Moshe Dayan, Yitzhak Rabin, Ehud Barak, Shaul Mofaz and Moshe Ya'alon) are also former Chiefs of Staff of the Israel Defense Forces.|$|R
